data.enText: an area of land that is almost surrounded by water but is joined to a larger piece of land
the Iberian peninsula (= Spain and Portugal)

simple_means.memory_skill: pen 近似，几乎 + insula 岛 → 近似岛 → 半岛

tr: a large mass of land projecting into a body of water

value.def: A peninsula is a long narrow piece of land which sticks out from a larger piece of land and is almost completely surrounded by water.

example.ex: ...the political situation in the Korean peninsula...
I had walked around the entire peninsula.

trans: 伊比利亚半岛；伊比利半岛

partsOfSpeech.dec: insul 岛屿 + ar …的 → 岛国的；偏狭的
insul 岛屿 + ate 做，造成，使… → 像岛屿般与世隔绝 → 隔离
insul 岛屿 + in …素 → 胰岛素
pen 近似 + insul 岛屿 + a → 似岛 → 半岛
pene〔 = pen〕近似，几乎 + plain 平原 → 准平原
pen 近似，几乎 + insula 岛 → 近似岛 → 半岛
pen 近似，几乎 + ultimate 最终 → 几乎是最后一个 → 倒数第二的
pen 近似，几乎 + umbra 影子 → 近似影子 → 半阴影
